# National Cycle Network Route 44

**National Cycle Network Route 44**, part of the [National Cycle Network](/National_Cycle_Network), is a 31.1 mile cycle route, ^[1](#cite_note-1) connecting [Shrewsbury](/Shrewsbury), [Shropshire](/Shropshire) with [Cinderford](/Cinderford), [Gloucestershire](/Gloucestershire). The part of the route from Shrewsbury to [Bromfield](/Bromfield,_Shropshire) is signed - the remainder of the route is currently unsigned.

The section from Shrewsbury to Leominster is advertised as the Six Castles Cycleway. The six castles on or near the route are (in geographical order from north to south): [Shrewsbury Castle](/Shrewsbury_Castle), [Bishop's Castle](/Bishop%27s_Castle), [Stokesay Castle](/Stokesay_Castle), [Ludlow Castle](/Ludlow_Castle), [Richard's Castle](/Richard%27s_Castle) and [Croft Castle](/Croft_Castle).

